an Michael -- tAppendix -- tNotes -- tThe Family Tree -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Kahans from Baku is a saga of a Russian Jewish family. Their story also provides an insight into the history of Jews in the Imperial Russian economy, especially in the oil industry. The entrepreneur and family patriarch, Chaim Kahan was a pious and enlightened man and a Zionist. His children followed in his footsteps in business as well as in policy, philanthropy and love of books. The Kahans from Baku takes us through a forced migration history in times of war and revolution and the 20th century’s totalitarian regimes telling a story of fortune and misfortune in economy and everyday life of one cohesive family over four generations in Russia, Germany, Denmark and France, ending up in Palestine and the United States of America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aAzerbaijan.  aForced migration.  aModern Jewish history.  aNazi Germany.  aRussian Revolution.  aZionist movement.  adiaspora.  afamily.  aoil industry.  apublishing houses.1 aGavrieli, Jonah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRosenberg, Noa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThemal, Uri, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076741408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is p